<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,895,1402]" box="[151,321,930,956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,321,930,956]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="1">
<taxonomicName box="[151,321,930,956]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,321,930,956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Scorpaenidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,895,1402]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
While a common coastal fish in other areas, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafinesque-Schmaltz, 1810" authorityName="Rafinesque-Schmaltz" authorityYear="1810" box="[724,1272,965,991]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notata">
<emphasis box="[724,932,965,990]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Scorpaena notata</emphasis>
Rafinesque-Schmaltz, 
<number box="[1213,1272,965,991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1810.0">1810</number>
</taxonomicName>
is found only deeper than 
<quantity box="[294,368,1002,1028]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
at Madeira and therefore not counted as a coastal species here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,895,1402]" box="[197,987,1040,1066]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[197,480,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
* 
<taxonomicName authority="Sauvage, 1878" authorityName="Sauvage" authorityYear="1878" box="[209,480,1040,1065]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canariensis">Scorpaena canariensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(Sauvage, 
<number box="[611,668,1040,1066]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1878.0">1878</number>
)—Canary Islands rockfish
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,895,1402]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Recorded from Madeira by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brito" box="[585,735,1077,1103]" pageId="9" pageNumber="24" refString="Brito, A. (1991) Catalogo de los peces de las Islas Canarias. F. Lemus, La Laguna. 230 pp." type="book" year="1991">
Brito (
<number box="[663,726,1077,1103]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. A previous record of 
<taxonomicName authority="Troschel, 1866" authorityName="Troschel" authorityYear="1866" box="[1002,1389,1077,1103]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis box="[1002,1203,1077,1102]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Scorpaena laevis</emphasis>
Troschel, 
<number box="[1330,1389,1077,1103]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1866.0">1866</number>
</taxonomicName>
(on the basis of 
<collectionCode box="[292,380,1114,1140]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">BMNH</collectionCode>
1984.3.6.551- 
<number box="[553,598,1114,1140]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="556.0">556</number>
) was re-identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[850,1015,1115,1140]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis box="[850,1015,1115,1140]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, there is no reliable record of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,249,1152,1177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis box="[151,249,1152,1177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Madeira. The specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[651,816,1152,1177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis box="[651,816,1152,1177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the collection of the 
<collectionCode box="[1098,1166,1152,1178]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mme0-gx6r" name="Museu Municipal do Funchal" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">MMF</collectionCode>
come from 
<quantity box="[1311,1386,1152,1178]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
and deeper. However, there are shallow water records of this species both at the Canary Islands and at the Azores; we therefore tentatively here list 
<taxonomicName box="[537,702,1227,1252]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis box="[537,702,1227,1252]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a coastal species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,895,1402]" box="[197,943,1264,1290]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[197,477,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
* 
<taxonomicName authority="Valenciennes, 1833" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1833" box="[209,477,1264,1289]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maderensis">Scorpaena maderensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Valenciennes, 
<number box="[654,709,1264,1290]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1833.0">1833</number>
—Madeira rockfish
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,895,1402]" box="[197,847,1301,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[197,594,1301,1327]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="porcus">
<emphasis box="[197,409,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Scorpaena porcus</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[538,594,1301,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</taxonomicName>
—Black scorpionfish
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,895,1402]" box="[255,630,1338,1364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">This record needs confirmation.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,895,1402]" box="[197,928,1376,1402]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[197,417,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
* 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[209,417,1376,1401]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scrofa">Scorpaena scrofa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[547,603,1376,1402]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1758.0">1758</number>
—Largescaled scorpionfish
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
